SUMMARY:Second Sunday Concerts: Teatro Nuovo
DESCRIPTION:Led by conductor/musicologist Will Crutchfield\, Teatro Nuovo – Italian for “new theater” – is a young organization devoted to cutting-edge interpretation of classic Italian opera. Since its debut in 2018\, Teatro Nuovo has presented thirteen operas by Rossini\, Donizetti\, Bellini\, Verdi\, Ricci\, and Mayr\, culminating in the modern premiere of Carolina Uccelli’s Anna di Resburgo\, which made the New York Times list of the 20 best Classical events for 2024. This year Teatro Nuovo will celebrate the bicentennial of Italian opera in America.\nThis concert will show how delving into forgotten traditions can animate the future of the art\, as Will Crutchfield and young vocal stars will perform virtuoso thrillers and heart-melting lyrics from the golden age of Italian Bel Canto. Don’t miss this exciting opportunity to hear some of opera’s newest rising stars!\nRegistrations are advised but some seats will be available just before the start of the concert. \nShare this:\n				Share on Facebook (Opens in new window)\n				Facebook\n			\n				Share on Bluesky (Opens in new window)\n				Bluesky\n			\n				Share on LinkedIn (Opens in new window)\n				LinkedIn\n			\n				Share on Threads (Opens in new window)\n				Threads\n			\n				Share on Nextdoor (Opens in new window)\n				Nextdoor\n			\n				Share on WhatsApp (Opens in new window)\n				WhatsApp\n			\n				Email a link to a friend (Opens in new window)\n				Email
URL:https://montclairlocal.news/event/second-sunday-concerts-teatro-nuovo/
LOCATION:Van Vleck House & Gardens\, 21 Van Vleck Street\, Montclair\, NJ\, 07042\, United States
CATEGORIES:General Events
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://montclairlocal.news/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/25.4.6-Teatro-Nuovo-YA-Concert_Levy-and-Tamborini-1.jpg
